research_municipality_step.notes: The City of Chandler, TX operates under a 'Type A' general law municipality with an aldermanic form of government, consisting of a mayor and five aldermen, also referred to as council members. All positions are elected at large for a two-year term. Information was primarily sourced from the City of Chandler's official website and the Texas Municipal League. One source listed a different council member (Jacob Stanton), but the official city website and Texas Municipal League consistently list Mark Hammack, which was prioritized for accuracy.
